<div id="p212" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#4&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=212#p212">2008-05-19 17:57:59</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89601">dave</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Editor</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEP 9: The Metadata Extension</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>There has been almost no commentary about this proposal.<br /><br />It has been implemented in uTorrent and the editor (me) is inclined to accept it.&nbsp; The &quot;accepted&quot; state is within the power delegated by the BDFL to editors.&nbsp; As it stands, only the BDFL can elevate something to &quot;final&quot; status.&nbsp; <br /><br />The proposal as it stands has references to LTEP.&nbsp; Thus although accepted this proposal cannot be finalized without also accepting LTEP or its derivative.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
